Preheat your oven to 220°C. Trim the @butternut squash{1} then halve lengthways and
scoop out the seeds. Chop it widthways into 2cm wide lengths, then chop into 2cm
chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the squash onto a large #baking tray{} in a single layer, drizzle with @oil{} and
season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Toss together to coat in the oil,
then roast on the top shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @red onion{1}, peel and then chop each half into five wedges.
Break the @feta cheese{100%g} up into roughly 2cm chunks.

When the squash has been in your oven for 20 mins, remove and add the onion wedges
to the tray. Mix around to combine everything together, then continue roasting until
the onion has softened and the squash is golden and soft, another ~{10-15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, lay in the
@British chicken thighs{4}(flat) and fry until golden, ~{6-7%minutes} on each side.
IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Once
cooked, remove the chicken to a #board{} and leave to rest for ~{2%minutes}.

Once everything is cooked, remove the veggies from the oven. Thinly slice the
chicken thighs. Pop the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @wild rocket{40%g} in a
large #bowl{} and mix together. Add in the squash, red onion and half the feta.
Toss everything together. Serve in bowls with the chicken on top and the remaining
feta sprinkled over. Enjoy!